<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><strong>Assumption</strong><br>
 For the <strong>RTGS payment rails</strong>, the <strong>fields sent to th=
e =E2=80=9CMake a Payment=E2=80=9D endpoint</strong> will follow the <stron=
g>same structure and mapping as existing domestic payment rails</strong> (e=
.g. <strong>NPP</strong>), <strong>with one key difference</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>For R<span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"01865a96-ae4c-4a=
67-a7a5-2927e753f00b">TGS paym</span>ents, we will <strong>send <code>payme=
ntProductId</code></strong></li>
<li><s>Instead of the <strong><code>serviceLevel</code></strong> currently =
used for NPP/domestic payments</s></li>
</ul>
<p>All other mandatory and optional fields are assumed to remain <strong>co=
nsistent with the existing domestic payment implementation</strong>, unless=
 explicitly stated otherwise.</p>
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"L201283" =
href=3D"/display/~L201283" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1864199723" data-link=
