<h2 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-KeyDecisions"><span>Key Decision=
s</span></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped relative-table confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 89.=
1507%;">
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 3.19846%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 18.5757%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 60.5247%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 13.5935%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 4.1211%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" scope=3D"col" class=3D"=
confluenceTh">Ref</th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" scope=3D"col" class=3D"=
confluenceTh">Decision</th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" scope=3D"col" class=3D"=
confluenceTh">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>Description</p>
</div></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" scope=3D"col" class=3D"=
confluenceTh">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>Decision made by</p>
</div></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" scope=3D"col" class=3D"=
confluenceTh">Status</th>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
#001</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
RTGS Aug release =E2=80=93&nbsp;<strong>Payment Details</strong> and <stron=
g>Transaction Details</strong> pages will remain <strong>AS=E2=80=91IS</str=
ong> with no UI or field changes.</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li><s>The&nbsp;<strong>same set of fields</strong> will continue to be dis=
played on both Payment Detail and Transaction Detail pages.</s></li>
<li><s><strong>No UI changes</strong> and <strong>no data field changes</st=
rong> are planned.</s></li>
</ul><p>Update: This Assumption is considered invalid as there are changes =
required on both mappings and UI.&nbsp;<br>
 e.g. UETR or potentially value date is expected to return in the payment e=
nquiry API.&nbsp;</p><p>And in the UI, there are a few display changes spec=
ifically for RTGS (refer to the Solution overview section in this document)=
</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M062280" =
href=3D"/display/~M062280" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1296375477" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"2" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Tejas Koteswara Rao</a>&nbsp;=
<br><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"L201283"=
 href=3D"/display/~L201283" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1864199723" data-lin=
ked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base=
-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Colin Yau</a>&nbsp;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Closed</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
#002</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Fields that are applicable to RTGS payment rail.&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>The below fields in Payment initiating API won't be applicable for RTGS =
payment.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" src=3D"9c03c7b3a4b81950fc4f85fdd32754=
a32420a103ab2450d9b66004e3e30fb155" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments=
/2271224574/image-2026-2-25_14-32-56.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=
=3D1771990377120&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-lin=
ked-resource-id=3D"2305565416" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-link=
ed-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image=
-2026-2-25_14-32-56.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.co=
m.au" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-=
container-id=3D"2271224574" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"47" a=
lt=3D"" width=3D"468" height=3D"378"></span></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M062280" =
href=3D"/display/~M062280" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1296375477" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"2" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Tejas Koteswara Rao</a>&nbsp;=
</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Closed</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
#003</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Payment Eligibility API will <strong>support RTGS</strong> as a payment =
rail.</p><p><br></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>The&nbsp;<strong>Payment Eligibility API</strong> is confirmed to suppo=
rt <strong>RTGS</strong>.</li>
<li>The <strong>responding payment scheme </strong>already supports RTGS as=
 a payment rail.</li>
<li>However, the <strong>internal logic within the Payment Eligibility API<=
/strong> still needs to be <strong>uplifted</strong> to fully enable RTGS h=
andling.</li>
<li>This is an <strong>implementation gap</strong>, not a functional limita=
tion of the payment method itself.</li>
</ul></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M058573" =
href=3D"/display/~M058573" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1125291984" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Ave Cahyadi</a>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Clarification provided by&nbsp;</p>
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M062091" =
href=3D"/display/~M062091" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1504078445" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Amandeep Singh</a>&nbsp;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Closed</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
#004</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"fe399006-b0a3-4584-849=
3-c0a2a7608be1">For </span><strong><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" da=
ta-ref=3D"fe399006-b0a3-4584-8493-c0a2a7608be1">RTGS payments</span></stron=
g><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"fe399006-b0a3-4584-8493=
-c0a2a7608be1">, </span><strong><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-=
ref=3D"fe399006-b0a3-4584-8493-c0a2a7608be1">Reference</span></strong><span=
 class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"fe399006-b0a3-4584-8493-c0a2a7=
608be1"> will not be used as the single displayed remittance field;&nbsp;</=
span><strong><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"fe399006-b0a=
3-4584-8493-c0a2a7608be1">Credit Description will be displayed</span></stro=
ng><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"fe399006-b0a3-4584-849=
3-c0a2a7608be1"> to ensure consistency</span>.</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li><p><strong>RTGS &amp; International payments</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Payments team confirmed that the relevant field for initiating RTGS &am=
p; International payments is '<strong>remittanceInformation.unstructured</s=
trong>' which we map to 'credit description' for NPP payments.&nbsp;</li>
<li>There is no requirement for the reference field (<strong>endToEndIdenti=
fication</strong>)</li>
</ul><p>Therefore...</p>
<ul>
<li>Make a payment page for RTGS &amp; international will capture a<span>&n=
bsp;</span><strong>credit description</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>field, not=
 a reference field</li>
<li>Transaction detail page for both inbound and outbound should show '<str=
ong>credit description</strong>' and should not show reference</li>
<li>Beneficiary payment template will not prepopulate on RTGS or Internatio=
nal payments (this is ok because we don't think it's as relevant for these =
payment types and we can uplift in future with a proper payment template so=
lution)</li>
</ul></li>
</ul></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M062280" =
href=3D"/display/~M062280" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1296375477" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"2" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Tejas Koteswara Rao</a>&nbsp;=
<br><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"L201283"=
 href=3D"/display/~L201283" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1864199723" data-lin=
ked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base=
-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Colin Yau</a>&nbsp;<br><a cl=
ass=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"F079288" href=3D"=
/display/~F079288" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1415102363" data-linked-resou=
rce-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"h=
ttps://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Melinda Jamieson</a>&nbsp;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Closed&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
#005</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>UETR Uniqueness</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p style=3D"font-weight: bold;"><strong>Problem Statement</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Channel is asked to generate the uuid and the uniqueness of the id is n=
ot guaranteed if it's generated in the <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker=
" data-ref=3D"370ebc05-3496-4d71-9cd9-6c1c0cf2e7d7">UI/EXP.</span>&nbsp;</l=
i>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong>Resolution</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>In case the UUID is found to be duplicated, there are existing process =
in GPP to rectify this, as confirmed by&nbsp;<a class=3D"confluence-userlin=
k user-mention" data-username=3D"L183776" href=3D"/display/~L183776" data-l=
inked-resource-id=3D"1296370911" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-li=
nked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.wes=
tpac.com.au">Muthukrishnan Ramaswamy</a> . so, this is not an issue to the =
overall process, and it has been agreed within the team it is not a concern=
.</li>
</ul>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"L183776" =
href=3D"/display/~L183776" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1296370911" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Muthukrishnan Ramaswamy</a> <=
a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"L201283" href=
=3D"/display/~L201283" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1864199723" data-linked-r=
esource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=
=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Colin Yau</a>&nbsp;<br><a class=
