<h3 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-Requirement(Channelrelated)">Req=
uirement (Channel related)</h3>
<p>-&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/ARTC/ART-38920%3A+Channels+Detailed+Requireme=
nts+for+RTGS+outward+payments#ART38920:ChannelsDetailedRequirementsforRTGSo=
utwardpayments-Requirements">ART-38920: Channels Detailed Requirements for =
RTGS outward payments#Requirements</a></p>
<h3 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-Non-FunctionalRequirementsTracea=
bility">Non-Functional Requirements Traceability</h3>
<p>NFRs for Account listing/ Account detail:</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC/Non-Functi=
onal+Requirements+-+Channels+Squad+NFRs#NonFunctionalRequirementsChannelsSq=
uadNFRs-Performanceperbusinessactivity-MVP" rel=3D"nofollow">Non-Functional=
 Requirements - Channels Squad NFRs - Westpac One Core - Westpac Enterprise=
 Confluence</a></p>
<h2 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-TechnicalDebt">Technical Debt</h=
2>
<p></p>
<p>N/A</p>
<h1 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-Solution"><span>Solution</span><=
/h1>
<h2 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-SolutionOverview"><span>Solution=
 Overview</span></h2>
<p>This change introduces <strong>RTGS (Real-Time Gross Settlement)</strong=
> support across the <strong>payment flow, eligibility, listing, transactio=
n details, and authorisation views</strong>, with specific UI, API, and dat=
a-handling impacts.<br>
 The implementation follows existing mappings where possible and introduces=
 RTGS-specific behaviour only where required.</p>
<h2 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-1.PaymentFlowChanges">1. Payment=
 Flow Changes</h2>
<h3 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-1.1SchemeEligibilityCheck">1.1 S=
cheme Eligibility Check</h3>
<p><strong>API - <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/A=
RTC/exp-galaxy-payment-v2#expgalaxypaymentv2-POST/schemeEligibility" rel=3D=
"nofollow">exp-galaxy-payment-v2#POST/schemeEligibility</a></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Downstream endpoint:<br><code><a href=3D"https://mesh.westpac.com.au/co=
mponents/apis/payment-scheme-eligibility-v1" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D=
"nofollow">https://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/payment-scheme-eligi=
bility-v1</a></code></li>
<li>RTGS will be returned under:<p><em><span class=3D"scriptor-textRun scri=
ptor-inline">paymentSchemes</span></em></p><strong>RTGS will be returned al=
ongside DE</strong>, if applicable.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Rules</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>If the <strong>creditor account is a PayID account</strong>, the <stron=
g>RTGS payment method must NOT be returned</strong>, even if RTGS is techni=
cally eligible.</li>
<li><strong>Payment method order</strong> in the response will be <strong>d=
efined by <a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"L2=
01283" href=3D"/display/~L201283" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1864199723" da=
ta-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" dat=
a-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Colin Yau</a>&nbsp;</s=
trong>
<ul>
<li><strong>Drafted version is per below:<br></strong></li>
<li><strong><a href=3D"/display/ARTC/ART-38920%3A+Channels+Detailed+Require=
ments+for+RTGS+outward+payments#ART38920:ChannelsDetailedRequirementsforRTG=
Soutwardpayments-Requirements">ART-38920: Channels Detailed Requirements fo=
r RTGS outward payments#Requirements</a> (#Req 2)</strong></li>
</ul></li>
<li>No mapping changes are required.</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p>Detail refer to Scheme Eligibility check SD:&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC/03.+SD%3A+=
Lookup+Scheme+eligibility+for+BSBs" rel=3D"nofollow">03. SD: Lookup Scheme =
eligibility for BSBs - Westpac One Core - Westpac Enterprise Confluence</a>=
</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Additional Payment Information Status / Event Status flow refers to Paym=
ent SD: <a href=3D"/display/ARTC/Inward+RTGS+and+ITT+%28AUD+only%29+Payment=
s#InwardRTGSandITT(AUDonly)Payments-EventStateDiagram">Inward RTGS and ITT =
(AUD only) Payments#EventStateDiagram</a>:</p>
<h3 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-1.2PaymentCreation(MakeaPayment)=
">1.2 Payment Creation (Make a Payment)</h3>
<h4 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-UETRGeneration">UETR Generation<=
/h4>
<ul>
<li>As discussed with the Payment team,=20
<ul>
<li><strong>UETR is generated by the <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" =
data-ref=3D"55efef7c-c99a-4112-886b-d4bfa1705fd0">UI/EXP</span></strong><sp=
an class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"55efef7c-c99a-4112-886b-d4bf=
a1705fd0">,</span> not by the payment team.</li>
<li>The payment team&nbsp;<strong>will not provide a new endpoint</strong> =
for ID generation.</li>
<li>As confirmed with <a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-us=
ername=3D"L183776" href=3D"/display/~L183776" data-linked-resource-id=3D"12=
96370911" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"u=
serinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Muthukrish=
nan Ramaswamy</a>&nbsp; and Maanasa<br>
<ul>
<li><strong>GUID Version 4</strong> will be used.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li>UETR must be:=20
<ul>
<li>Included in the <strong>payment payload</strong></li>
<li><strong>Not displayed</strong> on Maker or Checker screens</li>
</ul></li>
<li>UETR is expected to pass to the payment endpoint as identifier for RTGS=
 payment.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<h4 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-ReferencevsCreditDescription">Re=
ference vs Credit Description</h4>
<ul>
<li>For RTGS payments:=20
<ul>
<li><strong>Reference field is NOT shown in the UI</strong></li>
<li><strong>Credit Description field is shown instead</strong></li>
<li>Credit Description is <strong>limited to 140 characters</strong></li>
</ul></li>
<li>Backend <strong>mapping remains unchanged</strong></li>
</ul>
<h4 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-Cut-offtime">Cut-off time</h4>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Cut-off time to be sent from maker for RTGS , defaulted to 4pm, i.e. 16=
00</li>
</ul>
<h4 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-ServiceLevel">Service Level</h4>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Service level G001 will be used for both RTGS / International Payment. =
<span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><strong>(TBC)&nbsp;</strong></span></l=
i>
<li><s>Service level is not expected to be sent for RTGS payment, instead&n=
bsp;</s>payment product code should be sent for the RTGS payment rails. PIO=
 will derive the service level based on the Payment product Id.=20
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Payment prod<span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"0baf292c-=
7c7e-4f9d-8559-9a9655fd594c">uct id refers to the</span> below: (<a href=3D=
"/display/P3/Payment+Product+Store+Scenarios">Payment Product Store Scenari=
os</a>)</li>
<li><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluen=
ce-embedded-image confluence-external-resource" draggable=3D"false" alt=3D"=
image-2026-2-4_14-5-43.png" src=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/do=
wnload/attachments/1831312542/image-2026-2-4_14-5-43.png?version=3D1&amp;mo=
dificationDate=3D1770174343457&amp;api=3Dv2" data-image-src=3D"https://conf=
luence.srv.westpac.com.au/download/attachments/1831312542/image-2026-2-4_14=
-5-43.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1770174343457&amp;api=3Dv2"></=
span></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>CoP check remains as-is if BSB account beneficiary is added as part of =
the payment flow.</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-1.3PaymentLimitCheck">1.3 Paymen=
t Limit Check</h3>
<ul>
<li>RTGS payments are subject to <strong>existing payment limit checks</str=
ong></li>
<li>No new limit logic introduced</li>
<li>Behaviour is consistent with other payment rails</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-2.PaymentListing/Details">2. Pay=
ment Listing / Details</h2>
<h3 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-2.1PaymentDetail/PaymentListing(=
sentforprocessing)">2.1 Payment Detail / Payment Listing (sent for processi=
ng)</h3>
<h4 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-2.1.2PaymentListing:">2.1.2 Paym=
ent Listing:</h4>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);font-weight: bold;"><strong><span style=3D=
"color: rgb(255,0,0);">TBC if Value date to be shown is:</span></strong>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);font-weight: bold;"><strong><span style=3D=
"color: rgb(255,0,0);">Payment submission date (PODS) =E2=86=90 current val=
ue displayed&nbsp;</span></strong></li>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);font-weight: bold;"><strong><span style=3D=
"color: rgb(255,0,0);">Payment debit date (PODS)</span></strong></li>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);font-weight: bold;"><strong><span style=3D=
"color: rgb(255,0,0);">Payment processing date (PODS)</span></strong></li>
</ul></li>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);font-weight: bold;"><strong><span style=3D=
"color: rgb(255,0,0);">TBC new Payment information status could be returned=
, e.g. Pending</span></strong></li>
</ul>
<h4 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-2.1.2PaymentDetail:">2.1.2 Payme=
nt Detail:</h4>
<h4 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-EXPAPI:">EXP API:&nbsp;</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Reference field is NOT shown</strong> for RTGS</li>
<li><strong>Credit Description</strong> is displayed instead (max 140 chara=
cters)</li>
<li><strong>UETR</strong> to be displayed on screen</li>
<li><strong>Mapping remains unchanged</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>UI <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"f298448b-8ceb-4cd4-=
925f-43dc2938c986">Display refer to</span>: <a href=3D"https://confluence.s=
rv.westpac.com.au/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D1510495045" rel=3D"nofollo=
w">Payment Details UI- Payment Experience API Mapping</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Additional list of RTGS specific Reject reasons code might be returned a=
nd mapping is required.&nbsp; <strong>(Updates: No new Reject reason codes =
is introduced as part of the feature. Refer to Key Decision #006)</strong><=
/p>
<p><a href=3D"/display/ARTC/Error+Code+Mapping+for+Async+Response+Feature">=
Error Code Mapping for Async Response Feature</a></p>
<h3 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-2.2PaymentListing(AuthorisationV=
iew)">2.2 Payment Listing (Authorisation View)</h3>
<h4 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-NewColumn:Cut-offTime">New Colum=
n: Cut-off Time</h4>
<ul>
<li>A new column <strong>=E2=80=9CCut-off Time=E2=80=9D</strong> is introdu=
ced</li>
<li>Value: <strong>4:00 PM (AEST) - to be sent from the Maker and displayed=
 in the authorisation screens.</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Display Rules</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Cut-off time is returned <strong>only when current system time is betwe=
en 3:00 PM and 3:59 PM (AEST/AEDT) - <span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">T=
BC if it's a UI only change, if so the logic will be shifted to the UI.</sp=
an></strong></li>
<li>Outside this window:=20
<ul>
<li>Value must be <strong>empty / null</strong></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Responsibility</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Logic must be handled in the <strong>EXP API <a href=3D"https://conflue=
nce.srv.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC/galaxy-maker-checker-widget-exp-v1#gala=
xymakercheckerwidgetexpv1-POST/approvalWorkflowList" rel=3D"nofollow">POST =
/approvalWorkflowList</a> </strong>with new field (cut-off time) added in t=
he response.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-2.3TransactionDetailView">2.3 Tr=
ansaction Detail View</h3>
<ul>
<li>Same UI rules apply as payment listing:=20
<ul>
<li><strong>Reference hidden</strong></li>
<li><strong>Credit Description shown (140 chars)</strong></li>
</ul></li>
<li><p><strong>UETR</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><p>Displayed for:</p>
<ul>
<li><p><strong>Inbound RTGS</strong></p></li>
<li><p><strong>Outbound RTGS</strong></p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li><strong>Payment ID</strong>
<ul>
<li>Applicable <strong>only for outbound RTGS</strong></li>
<li>For inbound RTGS:=20
<ul>
<li>Downstream systems are expected to return <strong>null or empty</strong=
></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li>No mapping changes for EXP API is expected.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>UI Display refer to: <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/pa=
ges/viewpage.action?pageId=3D1998492331" rel=3D"nofollow">UI from EXP API M=
apping: Transaction Details</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"SD:DomesticRTGSOutward(Channels)-SequenceDiagram"><span>Sequence =
Diagram</span></h2>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
